{"id":6386,"date":"2024-10-13T19:10:01","date_gmt":"2024-10-13T19:10:01","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/gei.thomsuninfocare.com\/?p=6386"},"modified":"2025-01-16T12:02:15","modified_gmt":"2025-01-16T12:02:15","slug":"dr-sugaranjini-g","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.giridhareye.org\/dr-sugaranjini-g\/","title":{"rendered":"Dr. Sugaranjini G"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-1 fusion-flex-container has-pattern-background has-mask-background nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\" style=\"--awb-border-radius-top-left:0px;--awb-border-radius-top-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-left:0px;--awb-flex-wrap:wrap;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row fusion-flex-align-items-flex-start fusion-flex-content-wrap\" style=\"max-width:1414.4px;margin-left: calc(-4% \/ 2 );margin-right: calc(-4% \/ 2 );\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-0 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-flex-column\" style=\"--awb-padding-top:40px;--awb-padding-bottom:50px;--awb-bg-size:cover;--awb-width-large:100%;--awb-margin-top-large:0px;--awb-spacing-right-large:1.92%;--awb-margin-bottom-large:20px;--awb-spacing-left-large:1.92%;--awb-width-medium:100%;--awb-order-medium:0;--awb-spacing-right-medium:1.92%;--awb-spacing-left-medium:1.92%;--awb-width-small:100%;--awb-order-small:0;--awb-spacing-right-small:1.92%;--awb-spacing-left-small:1.92%;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-column-has-shadow fusion-flex-justify-content-flex-start fusion-content-layout-column\"><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-1 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"--awb-margin-bottom:0px;\"><h3 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Educational Qualifications<\/h3><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator\" style=\"align-self: flex-start;margin-right:auto;margin-bottom:20px;width:100%;max-width:20%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;--awb-sep-color:var(--awb-color4);border-color:var(--awb-color4);border-top-width:2px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-1\"><p>Dr. Sugaranjini G is a highly qualified ophthalmologist who began her medical journey with an MBBS from Sri Devaraj Urs Medical College, Kolar, Karnataka, in 2011. She went on to earn a Diploma in Ophthalmology (DO) from Sri Devaraj Urs Academy of Higher Education and Research in 2015. Further advancing her expertise, she completed her DNB in Ophthalmology at Narayana Nethralaya, Bangalore, between 2017 and 2019. She has also undergone extensive fellowship training, including a fellowship in General Ophthalmology at Bangalore West Lions Super Specialty Eye Hospital (2015-2016), and a fellowship in Cornea, Refractive Surgery, and Ocular Surface Disorders at Giridhar Eye Institute (2019-2022). Additionally, she pursued short-term phaco training at Susrut Eye Foundation and Research Centre in 2019.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-2 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:40px;--awb-margin-bottom:0px;\"><h3 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Specialisation<\/h3><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator\" style=\"align-self: flex-start;margin-right:auto;margin-bottom:20px;width:100%;max-width:20%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;--awb-sep-color:var(--awb-color4);border-color:var(--awb-color4);border-top-width:2px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-2\"><p>Dr. Sugaranjini specializes in Cornea, Refractive Surgery, Ocular Surface Disorders, Dry Eye, and Cataract Surgery. She has a keen interest in advanced treatments such as corneal transplantation, corneal imaging, and managing complex conditions like Sjogren&#8217;s syndrome-associated dry eye, recurrent corneal erosion syndrome, and sequelae of Steven Johnson syndrome. Her dedication extends to addressing ocular allergies in children, making her a versatile expert in her field.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-3 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:40px;--awb-margin-bottom:0px;\"><h3 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Work Experience<\/h3><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator\" style=\"align-self: flex-start;margin-right:auto;margin-bottom:20px;width:100%;max-width:20%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;--awb-sep-color:var(--awb-color4);border-color:var(--awb-color4);border-top-width:2px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-3\"><p>Currently, Dr. Sugaranjini serves as an Associate Consultant at Giridhar Eye Institute, Kochi. Her experience has equipped her with a comprehensive skill set, enabling her to provide expert care in her specialized areas.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-4 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:40px;--awb-margin-bottom:0px;\"><h3 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Publications<\/h3><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator\" style=\"align-self: flex-start;margin-right:auto;margin-bottom:20px;width:100%;max-width:20%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;--awb-sep-color:var(--awb-color4);border-color:var(--awb-color4);border-top-width:2px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-4\"><p>Dr. Sugaranjini has contributed to the field of ophthalmology through various published works, focusing on topics like keratoconus, advanced corneal imaging, corneal transplants, ocular surface disorders, and retinal pathologies, including retinoschisis and choroidal osteoma. Her research has been featured in prestigious national and international journals such as the Indian Journal of Ophthalmology, Journal of Refractive Surgery, and the Canadian Journal of Ophthalmology.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-5 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:40px;--awb-margin-bottom:0px;\"><h3 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Achievements<\/h3><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator\" style=\"align-self: flex-start;margin-right:auto;margin-bottom:20px;width:100%;max-width:20%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;--awb-sep-color:var(--awb-color4);border-color:var(--awb-color4);border-top-width:2px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-5\"><p>Dr. Sugaranjini&#8217;s accomplishments include receiving a Gold Medal in Ophthalmology in 2015 and the Best Paper Award at KSOS in 2023. She has presented numerous scientific papers at renowned ophthalmology conferences across India, such as AIOS, KERACON, KSOS, and KOS, as well as at international conferences in Asia and Europe. Additionally, she contributes to the academic community as a peer reviewer for the Indian Journal of Ophthalmology.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-2 fusion-flex-container nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling fusion-animated\" style=\"--awb-background-position:right center;--awb-border-sizes-top:0px;--awb-border-sizes-bottom:0px;--awb-border-sizes-left:0px;--awb-border-sizes-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-top-left:0px;--awb-border-radius-top-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-left:0px;--awb-padding-top:30px;--awb-padding-right:30px;--awb-padding-bottom:65px;--awb-padding-left:30px;--awb-padding-top-small:125.863px